</div><div class="t m1f5 x31 h2d y555 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">These examples prove, consequently, that &quot;the Lord knows how to </div><div class="t m344 x6d h2d y556 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">rescue the godly from trial, and to keep the unrighteous under punish-</div><div class="t m26a x6d h2d y5d8 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment until the day of judgment, and especially those who indulge in </div><div class="t m689 x6d h2d y8a0 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lust of defiling passion and despise authority&quot; (2 Pet. 2:9, 10, </div><div class="t m68a x6d h2d y6df ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">RSV). </div><div class="t m68b x4a he y559 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DISCUSSION QUESTIONS: </div><div class="t m55c x31 he y891 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m3e1 xc4 he y55a ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sometimes God intervenes in marvelous ways, other times </div><div class="t m68c x6 he y20 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nature, or even evil itself, seems to be allowed to run its </div><div class="t m264 x6 he y55c ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">course. Considering the stories read this week, why must we </div><div class="t m1ab x6 he y8a1 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be very careful about judging someone&apos;s spiritual walk by his </div><div class="t m245 x6 he y8a2 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">or her fate? In other words, how easy it would be, for in-</div><div class="t m68d x6 he y55f ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">stance, to think that John the Baptist did something evil to </div><div class="t m2b5 x6 he y8a3 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">deserve his fate? </div><div class="t m327 x31 he y8a4 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m68e xc4 he y8a4 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Though this </div><div class="t m68f xa4 h2d y562 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">week&apos;s </div><div class="t m690 xab he y562 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lesson dealt with those who were </div><div class="t m3f6 x6 he y8a5 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">martyrs for Christ, it has been said that &quot;It&apos;s easier to </div><div class="t m691 x6 he y8a6 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">die for God than live for Him.&quot; What does that mean? </div><div class="t m147 x40 he y8a7 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m1a2 x6 he y565 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As mentioned at the beginning of the week, the word </div><div class="t m252 xc5 he y565 ff7 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">martyr </div><div class="t m692 x6 he y8a8 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">comes from the same word as </div><div class="t m5dc x2c he y566 ff7 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">witness. </div><div class="t m5ec x29 he y566 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Martyrs do, indeed, </div><div class="t m379 x6 he y567 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">witness for their faith. What about those who die in obscu-</div><div class="t m5e6 x6 he y569 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">rity for the Lord? In what ways are they witnesses? To </div><div class="t m2bd x6 he y8a9 ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">whom do they witness, and when? </div><div class="t m693 x69 he y8aa ff6 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUMMARY: </div><div class="t m694 x4d h2d y77a ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Those called to serve Christ might have to do so at </div><div class="t m695 x69 h2d y6ea ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the cost of their lives. Considering the reward, the price is cheap </div><div class="t m696 x69 h2d y6d4 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">enough. </div><div class="t m1d4 x69 h2d y37d ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">86 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
